sec.p:
The proposed PTO is a direct-drive mechanical system composed of a mechanical conversion system, a gearbox, a flywheel, and a rotary electric generator located on the topside deck (Figure 2). The buoy’s vertical movement is transmitted via a heave stem to the mechanical conversion system composed of a pulley, gears, and a backstop system. The pulley converts the vertical movement of the buoy into oscillating rotational motion. The velocity of the pulley is defined by1φ˙=z˙/r\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\dot{\varphi }=\dot{z}/r$$\end{document}where z˙\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\dot{z}$$\end{document} is the vertical velocity of the buoy and r\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$r$$\end{document} is radius of the pulley. The backstop system guarantees the unidirectional rotation delivered to the electric generator. A gearbox is used to increase the delivered speed to the generator. A flywheel is also used to store kinetic energy and smooth the generator’s energy delivery. Coupling condition of the PTO system and the cylindrical buoy is the same as described in Sanada et al. (2012), Bihn et al. (2016), and Liang et al. (2017). The buoy and PTO are coupled only when the rotational speed generated by the buoy is higher than rotational speed of the electrical generator; otherwise, they are uncoupled. 
Figure 2
Direct-drive mechanical PTO system

